<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-13T08:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-13T08:35:00-05:00" n="41" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d41">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">124.90H/67: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-13T17:00:00+03:25">March 13,
                                    1942—5 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received March 13—1:47 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>67. Supplementing my No. 64, March 12, I believe that if Department
                            agrees to name a Minister Plenipotentiary to Afghanistan it may be
                            possible to obtain consent of Afghan Government to Thayer’s proceeding
                            to Kabul for purpose of opening Legation.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>